,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":2819,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":25504,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":2819},\"output_tokens\":9,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYnmAoAG5KvH2DHMQ339z\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"17c942f7-4eff-48a6-90a0-00e1b9e578ff\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:20:12.368Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"17c942f7-4eff-48a6-90a0-00e1b9e578ff\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"c102346f-9f39-4c3a-ac22-b65d93ea0d33\",\"version\":\"2.1.71\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage-local-only\",\"slug\":\"giggly-spinning-dahl\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"PostToolUse\",\"hookName\":\"PostToolUse:Read\",\"command\":\"callback\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_012ovbn4iys7rQUQJYq2ALp3\",\"toolUseID\":\"toolu_012ovbn4iys7rQUQJYq2ALp3\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:20:12.381Z\",\"uuid\":\"c948c40d-613a-4247-a94f-d2da453bf65b\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"17c942f7-4eff-48a6-90a0-00e1b9e578ff\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"c102346f-9f39-4c3a-ac22-b65d93ea0d33\",\"version\":\"2.1.71\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage-local-only\",\"slug\":\"giggly-spinning-dahl\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_012ovbn4iys7rQUQJYq2ALp3\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→---\\n     2→name: e2e-triage\\n     3→description: Triage E2E test failures — run locally with mise or via CI re-runs, classify flaky vs real bug. Local mode presents findings and applies fixes in-place; CI mode creates PRs for flaky fixes and prints reports for real bugs.\\n     4→---\\n     5→\\n     6→# E2E Triage\\n     7→\\n     8→Triage E2E test failures with **re-run verification**. Operates in two modes (auto-detected), analyzes artifacts, and re-runs failing tests to distinguish flaky from real bugs. **Local mode** presents findings interactively and applies fixes directly in the working tree. **CI mode** creates batched PRs for flaky fixes and prints structured reports for real bugs (no GitHub issues).\\n     9→\\n    10→## Mode Detection\\n    11→\\n    12→The two modes share the same analysis and classification logic but differ in how results are presented and acted upon. Local mode is interactive (user reviews findings, chooses what to fix); CI mode is automated (PRs and issues created directly).\\n    13→\\n    14→- **CI mode**: `WORKFLOW_RUN_ID` env var is set (injected by `e2e-triage.yml`)\\n    15→- **Local mode**: No `WORKFLOW_RUN_ID` — user invokes `/e2e-triage` manually\\n    16→\\n    17→---\\n    18→\\n    19→## Local Mode\\n    20→\\n    21→### Step L1: Parse User Input\\n    22→\\n    23→The user provides one or more of:\\n    24→- **Test name(s)** — e.g., `TestInteractiveMultiStep`\\n    25→- **`--agent <agent>`** — optional, defaults to all agents that previously failed\\n    26→- **A local artifact path** — skip straight to analysis of existing artifacts\\n    27→\\n    28→**Cost warning:** Real E2E tests consume API tokens. Before running, confirm with the user unless they provided specific test names (implying intent to run).\\n    29→\\n    30→### Step L2: First Run\\n    31→\\n    32→```bash\\n    33→mise run test:e2e --agent <agent> <TestName>\\n    34→```\\n    35→\\n    36→Capture the artifact directory from the `artifacts: <path>` output line.\\n    37→\\n    38→### Step L3: Re-run on Failure\\n    39→\\n    40→If the test **passes** on first run: report as passing, done for this test.\\n    41→\\n    42→If the test **fails**: run a **second time** with the same parameters.\\n    43→\\n    44→### Step L4: Tiebreaker (if needed)\\n    45→\\n    46→If results are **split** (1 pass, 1 fail): run a **third time** as tiebreaker.\\n    47→\\n    48→### Step L5: Collect Results\\n    49→\\n    50→For each test+agent pair, record: `(test, agent, run_1_result, run_2_result, [run_3_result])`\\n    51→\\n    52→Proceed to **Shared Analysis** (Step 1 below).\\n    53→\\n    54→---\\n    55→\\n    56→## CI Mode\\n    57→\\n    58→### Step C1: Download Artifacts\\n    59→\\n    60→**If given a run ID, URL, or \\\"latest\\\":**\\n    61→```bash\\n    62→artifact_dir=$(scripts/download-e2e-artifacts.sh <input>)\\n    63→```\\n    64→\\n    65→**If `WORKFLOW_RUN_ID` is set (automated trigger):**\\n    66→```bash\\n    67→artifact_dir=\\\"e2e/artifacts/ci-${WORKFLOW_RUN_ID}\\\"\\n    68→```\\n    69→\\n    70→The download step in the workflow has already placed artifacts there.\\n    71→\\n    72→### Step C2: Identify Failures\\n    73→\\n    74→For each agent subdirectory in the artifact root:\\n    75→1. Read `report.nocolor.txt` — list failed tests with error messages, file:line references\\n    76→2. Skip agents with zero failures\\n    77→3. Build failure list: `[(test_name, agent, error_line, duration, file:line)]`\\n    78→\\n    79→### Step C3: Re-run Failing Tests via CI\\n    80→\\n    81→For each failing test+agent pair, **sequentially**:\\n    82→\\n    83→1. **Trigger re-run:**\\n    84→   ```bash\\n    85→   gh workflow run e2e-isolated.yml -f agent=<agent> -f test=<TestName>\\n    86→   ```\\n    87→\\n    88→2. **Wait for run to register** (~5s), then find the run ID:\\n    89→   ```bash\\n    90→   gh run list -w e2e-isolated.yml -L 1 --json databaseId -q '.[0].databaseId'\\n    91→   ```\\n    92→\\n    93→3. **Poll until complete** (check every 30s, timeout after 25 minutes):\\n    94→   ```bash\\n    95→   gh run view <run-id> --json status,conclusion\\n    96→   ```\\n    97→\\n    98→4. **Download re-run artifacts:**\\n    99→   ```bash\\n   100→   gh run download <run-id> --dir <rerun-artifact-dir>\\n   101→   ```\\n   102→\\n   103→5. **Repeat for a second re-run** (same test+agent).\\n   104→\\n   105→### Step C4: Collect Results\\n   106→\\n   107→For each test+agent pair, record: `(test, agent, original_result, rerun_1_result, rerun_2_result)`\\n   108→\\n   109→Proceed to **Shared Analysis** (Step 1 below).\\n   110→\\n   111→---\\n   112→\\n   113→## Shared Analysis & Classification\\n   114→\\n   115→### Step 1: Analyze Each Failure\\n   116→\\n   117→For each failure, follow the **Debugging Workflow** in `.claude/skills/debug-e2e/SKILL.md` (steps 2-5: console.log → test source → entire.log → deep dive). Collect:\\n   118→- What the agent actually did (from console.log)\\n   119→- What was expected (from test source)\\n   120→- CLI-level errors or anomalies (from entire.log)\\n   121→- Repo/checkpoint state (from git-log.txt, git-tree.txt, checkpoint-metadata/)\\n   122→\\n   123→### Step 2: Classify Each Failure\\n   124→\\n   125→Use **re-run results as the primary signal**, supplemented by artifact analysis.\\n   126→\\n   127→#### Re-run signals (strongest):\\n   128→\\n   129→| Original | Re-run 1 | Re-run 2 | Classification |\\n   130→|----------|----------|----------|----------------|\\n   131→| FAIL | FAIL (same error) | FAIL (same error) | **real-bug** OR **flaky (test-bug)** — see below |\\n   132→| FAIL | PASS | PASS | **flaky** |\\n   133→| FAIL | PASS | FAIL | **flaky** (non-deterministic) |\\n   134→| FAIL | FAIL | PASS | **flaky** (non-deterministic) |\\n   135→| FAIL | FAIL (different error) | FAIL (different error) | **needs deeper analysis** — examine artifacts |\\n   136→\\n   137→**Important: Consistent failures can still be `flaky` (test-bug).** When all re-runs fail, check *where* the root cause is:\\n   138→- Root cause in `cmd/entire/cli/` → **real-bug** (product code is broken)\\n   139→- Root cause in `e2e/` (test infra, test helpers, tmux setup, env propagation) → **flaky (test-bug)** — the CLI works fine, the test is broken\\n   140→\\n   141→#### Strong `real-bug` signals (root cause must be in `cmd/entire/cli/`, not `e2e/`):\\n   142→\\n   143→- `entire.log` contains `\\\"level\\\":\\\"ERROR\\\"` or panic/stack traces from CLI code\\n   144→- Checkpoint metadata structurally corrupt (malformed JSON, missing `checkpoint_id`/`strategy`)\\n   145→- Session state file missing or malformed when expected\\n   146→- Hooks did not fire at all (no `hook invoked` log entries)\\n   147→- Shadow/metadata branch has wrong tree structure\\n   148→- Same test fails across 3+ agents with same non-timeout symptom\\n   149→- Error references CLI code (panic in `cmd/entire/cli/`)\\n   150→\\n   151→**Key question:** Is the bug in `cmd/entire/cli/` (product code) or in `e2e/` (test code)? Only the former is a `real-bug`.\\n   152→\\n   153→#### Strong `flaky` signals (unless overridden by real-bug):\\n   154→\\n   155→**Agent behavior (non-deterministic):**\\n   156→- `signal: killed` (timeout)\\n   157→- `context deadline exceeded` or `WaitForCheckpoint.*exceeded deadline`\\n   158→- Agent asked for confirmation instead of acting\\n   159→- Agent created file at wrong path / wrong name\\n   160→- Agent produced no output\\n   161→- Agent committed when it shouldn't have (or vice versa)\\n   162→- Duration near timeout limit\\n   163→\\n   164→**Test-bug (consistent failure, but root cause is in `e2e/` not `cmd/entire/cli/`):**\\n   165→- Agent \\\"Not logged in\\\" / auth errors → test env setup doesn't propagate auth credentials\\n   166→- Env vars not propagated to agent session → tmux/test harness bug\\n   167→- Error references test code (`e2e/`) not CLI code (`cmd/entire/cli/`)\\n   168→- Test helper logic errors (wrong assertions, bad globs, incorrect expected values)\\n   169→- Consistent failure BUT root cause traced to `e2e/` code, not `cmd/entire/cli/`\\n   170→- Test setup/teardown issues (missing git config, temp dir cleanup, port conflicts)\\n   171→\\n   172→#### Ambiguous cases:\\n   173→\\n   174→Read `entire.log` carefully:\\n   175→- If hooks fired correctly and metadata is valid -> lean **flaky**\\n   176→- If hooks fired but produced wrong results -> lean **real-bug**\\n   177→\\n   178→### Step 3: Cross-Agent Correlation\\n   179→\\n   180→Before acting, check correlations using re-run data:\\n   181→- Same test fails for 3+ agents, all re-runs also fail -> strong **real-bug**\\n   182→- Same test fails for multiple agents, but re-runs pass -> **flaky** (shared prompt issue)\\n   183→- One agent fails consistently, others pass -> agent-specific issue (still **real-bug** if re-runs confirm)\\n   184→\\n   185→### Step 4a: Take Action — Local Mode\\n   186→\\n   187→In local mode, present findings interactively. **Do not** create branches, PRs, or GitHub issues.\\n   188→\\n   189→#### Present Findings Report\\n   190→\\n   191→For each test+agent pair, print a findings block:\\n   192→\\n   193→```\\n   194→## <TestName> (<agent>) — <classification>\\n   195→\\n   196→**Re-run results:** original=FAIL, rerun1=PASS, rerun2=PASS\\n   197→**Evidence:**\\n   198→- <1-2 sentence summary of what went wrong>\\n   199→- <key artifact evidence: entire.log excerpt, console.log excerpt, etc.>\\n   200→```\\n   201→\\n   202→#### For `flaky` failures: describe the proposed fix\\n   203→\\n   204→For agent-behavior flaky issues, fixes typically modify test prompts. For test-bug flaky issues, fixes target `e2e/` infrastructure code (harness setup, helpers, env propagation).\\n   205→\\n   206→```\\n   207→**Proposed fix:** <description>\\n   208→  - File: <path to test file or e2e infrastructure file>\\n   209→  - Change: <what will be modified — e.g., append \\\"Do not ask for confirmation\\\" to prompt, or fix env propagation in NewTmuxSession>\\n   210→```\\n   211→\\n   212→Common flaky fixes (same as CI mode):\\n   213→- Agent asked for confirmation -> append \\\"Do not ask for confirmation\\\" to prompt\\n   214→- Agent wrote to wrong path -> be more explicit about paths in prompt\\n   215→- Agent committed when shouldn't -> add \\\"Do not commit\\\" to prompt\\n   216→- Checkpoint wait timeout -> increase timeout argument\\n   217→- Agent timeout (signal: killed) -> increase per-test timeout, simplify prompt\\n   218→- Auth/env not propagated -> fix test harness env setup in `e2e/` code\\n   219→- Test helper bug (wrong assertion, bad glob) -> fix test helper in `e2e/`\\n   220→- tmux session setup issue -> fix `NewTmuxSession` or session config in `e2e/`\\n   221→\\n   222→#### For `real-bug` failures: describe root cause analysis\\n   223→\\n   224→```\\n   225→**Root cause analysis:**\\n   226→  - Component: <hooks | session | checkpoint | strategy | agent>\\n   227→  - Suspected location: <file:function>\\n   228→  - Description: <what's wrong and why>\\n   229→  - Proposed fix: <what code change would address it>\\n   230→```\\n   231→\\n   232→#### Ask the user\\n   233→\\n   234→Prompt the user:\\n   235→\\n   236→> **Should I fix these?**\\n   237→> - [list of tests with classifications]\\n   238→> - You can select all, specific tests, or skip.\\n   239→\\n   240→Wait for user response before proceeding.\\n   241→\\n   242→#### Apply fixes (if user approves)\\n   243→\\n   244→For **flaky** fixes the user approved:\\n   245→1. Apply fixes directly in the working tree (no branch creation)\\n   246→2. Run verification:\\n   247→   ```bash\\n   248→   mise run test:e2e:canary   # Must pass\\n   249→   mise run fmt && mise run lint\\n   250→   ```\\n   251→3. If canary fails, investigate and adjust. Report what happened to the user.\\n   252→\\n   253→For **real-bug** fixes the user approved:\\n   254→1. Apply the fix directly in the working tree (no branch creation)\\n   255→2. Run relevant tests to verify:\\n   256→   ```bash\\n   257→   mise run test        # Unit tests\\n   258→   mise run test:e2e:canary  # Canary tests\\n   259→   ```\\n   260→3. Report results to the user.\\n   261→\\n   262→### Step 4b: Take Action — CI Mode\\n   263→\\n   264→#### For `flaky` failures: Batched PR\\n   265→\\n   266→1. Create branch `fix/e2e-flaky-<run-id-or-date>`\\n   267→2. Apply fixes to ALL flaky test files (one branch, one PR):\\n   268→   - Agent asked for confirmation -> append \\\"Do not ask for confirmation\\\" to prompt\\n   269→   - Agent wrote to wrong path -> be more explicit about paths in prompt\\n   270→   - Agent committed when shouldn't -> add \\\"Do not commit\\\" to prompt\\n   271→   - Checkpoint wait timeout -> increase timeout argument\\n   272→   - Agent timeout (signal: killed) -> increase per-test timeout, simplify prompt\\n   273→   - Auth/env not propagated -> fix test harness env setup in `e2e/` code\\n   274→   - Test helper bug (wrong assertion, bad glob) -> fix test helper in `e2e/`\\n   275→   - tmux session setup issue -> fix `NewTmuxSession` or session config in `e2e/`\\n   276→3. Run verification:\\n   277→   ```bash\\n   278→   mise run test:e2e:canary   # Must pass\\n   279→   mise run fmt && mise run lint\\n   280→   ```\\n   281→4. If canary fails, investigate and adjust. If unfixable, fall back to issue creation.\\n   282→5. Commit and create PR:\\n   283→   ```bash\\n   284→   gh pr create \\\\\\n   285→     --title \\\"fix(e2e): make flaky tests more resilient\\\" \\\\\\n   286→     --body \\\"<structured body with per-test changes, re-run evidence, run link>\\\"\\n   287→   ```\\n   288→\\n   289→#### For `real-bug` failures: CI Report\\n   290→\\n   291→Print a structured report to stdout (visible in CI logs / GitHub Actions step output). **Do NOT create GitHub issues or comments.**\\n   292→\\n   293→```\\n   294→══════════════════════════════════════════════════════\\n   295→REAL BUG REPORT: <TestName> (<agent(s)>)\\n   296→══════════════════════════════════════════════════════\\n   297→\\n   298→Re-run results: original=FAIL, rerun1=FAIL, rerun2=FAIL\\n   299→CI run: <run URL>\\n   300→\\n   301→FAILURE SUMMARY\\n   302→  Expected: <what should have happened>\\n   303→  Actual:   <what happened instead>\\n   304→\\n   305→ROOT CAUSE ANALYSIS\\n   306→  Component: <hooks | session | checkpoint | strategy | agent>\\n   307→  Location:  <file:function>\\n   308→  Description: <what's wrong and why>\\n   309→\\n   310→KEY EVIDENCE\\n   311→  entire.log: <relevant excerpts>\\n   312→  console.log: <relevant excerpts>\\n   313→  git state: <relevant details>\\n   314→\\n   315→REPRODUCTION STEPS\\n   316→  1. <step>\\n   317→  2. <step>\\n   318→\\n   319→SUSPECTED FIX\\n   320→  File: <path>\\n   321→  Function: <name>\\n   322→  Reason: <why this is the likely fix location>\\n   323→══════════════════════════════════════════════════════\\n   324→```\\n   325→\\n   326→### Step 5: Summary Report\\n   327→\\n   328→#### Local mode\\n   329→\\n   330→Print a summary table:\\n   331→```\\n   332→| Test | Agent(s) | Re-runs | Classification | Action Taken |\\n   333→|------|----------|---------|---------------|-------------|\\n   334→| TestFoo | claude-code | FAIL/PASS/PASS | flaky | Fixed in working tree |\\n   335→| TestBar | all agents | FAIL/FAIL/FAIL | real-bug | Fix applied, tests passing |\\n   336→| TestBaz | opencode | FAIL/PASS/FAIL | flaky | Skipped (user declined) |\\n   337→```\\n   338→\\n   339→No `triage-summary.json` is written in local mode.\\n   340→\\n   341→#### CI mode\\n   342→\\n   343→Print a summary table:\\n   344→```\\n   345→| Test | Agent(s) | Re-runs | Classification | Action | Link |\\n   346→|------|----------|---------|---------------|--------|------|\\n   347→| TestFoo | claude-code | FAIL/PASS/PASS | flaky | PR #123 | url |\\n   348→| TestBar | all agents | FAIL/FAIL/FAIL | real-bug | Report (see CI logs) | — |\\n   349→| TestBaz | opencode | FAIL/PASS/FAIL | flaky | PR #123 | url |\\n   350→```\\n   351→\\n   352→The \\\"Re-runs\\\" column shows original/rerun1/rerun2 results.\\n   353→\\n   354→**Write `triage-summary.json`** in the artifact directory for Slack notifications:\\n   355→\\n   356→```bash\\n   357→cat > \\\"${ARTIFACT_DIR}/triage-summary.json\\\" << 'TEMPLATE'\\n   358→{\\n   359→  \\\"actions\\\": [\\n   360→    {\\n   361→      \\\"test\\\": \\\"TestName\\\",\\n   362→      \\\"agents\\\": [\\\"claude-code\\\", \\\"opencode\\\"],\\n   363→      \\\"classification\\\": \\\"flaky|real-bug\\\",\\n   364→      \\\"rerun_results\\\": [\\\"FAIL\\\", \\\"PASS\\\", \\\"PASS\\\"],\\n   365→      \\\"action_type\\\": \\\"pr|report\\\",\\n   366→      \\\"action_description\\\": \\\"PR #123|Report (see CI logs)\\\",\\n   367→      \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/123\\\"\\n   368→    }\\n   369→  ]\\n   370→}\\n   371→TEMPLATE\\n   372→```\\n   373→\\n   374→Each entry in `actions` corresponds to one row in the summary table. Include all failures that had an action taken. The `link` field must be the full URL to the PR or issue.\\n   375→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"2e21897e-3fce-4d87-9cd1-087a8ca8e0a1\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:20:12.381Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/.claude/skills/e2e-triage/SKILL.md\",\"content\":\"---\\nname: e2e-triage\\ndescription: Triage E2E test failures — run locally with mise or via CI re-runs, classify flaky vs real bug. Local mode presents findings and applies fixes in-place; CI mode creates PRs for flaky fixes and prints reports for real bugs.\\n---\\n\\n# E2E Triage\\n\\nTriage E2E test failures with **re-run verification**. Operates in two modes (auto-detected), analyzes artifacts, and re-runs failing tests to distinguish flaky from real bugs. **Local mode** presents findings interactively and applies fixes directly in the working tree. **CI mode** creates batched PRs for flaky fixes and prints structured reports for real bugs (no GitHub issues).\\n\\n## Mode Detection\\n\\nThe two modes share the same analysis and classification logic but differ in how results are presented and acted upon. Local mode is interactive (user reviews findings, chooses what to fix); CI mode is automated (PRs and issues created directly).\\n\\n- **CI mode**: `WORKFLOW_RUN_ID` env var is set (injected by `e2e-triage.yml`)\\n- **Local mode**: No `WORKFLOW_RUN_ID` — user invokes `/e2e-triage` manually\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Local Mode\\n\\n### Step L1: Parse User Input\\n\\nThe user provides one or more of:\\n- **Test name(s)** — e.g., `TestInteractiveMultiStep`\\n- **`--agent <agent>`** — optional, defaults to all agents that previously failed\\n- **A local artifact path** — skip straight to analysis of existing artifacts\\n\\n**Cost warning:** Real E2E tests consume API tokens. Before running, confirm with the user unless they provided specific test names (implying intent to run).\\n\\n### Step L2: First Run\\n\\n```bash\\nmise run test:e2e --agent <agent> <TestName>\\n```\\n\\nCapture the artifact directory from the `artifacts: <path>` output line.\\n\\n### Step L3: Re-run on Failure\\n\\nIf the test **passes** on first run: report as passing, done for this test.\\n\\nIf the test **fails**: run a **second time** with the same parameters.\\n\\n### Step L4: Tiebreaker (if needed)\\n\\nIf results are **split** (1 pass, 1 fail): run a **third time** as tiebreaker.\\n\\n### Step L5: Collect Results\\n\\nFor each test+agent pair, record: `(test, agent, run_1_result, run_2_result, [run_3_result])`\\n\\nProceed to **Shared Analysis** (Step 1 below).\\n\\n---\\n\\n## CI Mode\\n\\n### Step C1: Download Artifacts\\n\\n**If given a run ID, URL, or \\\"latest\\\":**\\n```bash\\nartifact_dir=$(scripts/download-e2e-artifacts.sh <input>)\\n```\\n\\n**If `WORKFLOW_RUN_ID` is set (automated trigger):**\\n```bash\\nartifact_dir=\\\"e2e/artifacts/ci-${WORKFLOW_RUN_ID}\\\"\\n```\\n\\nThe download step in the workflow has already placed artifacts there.\\n\\n### Step C2: Identify Failures\\n\\nFor each agent subdirectory in the artifact root:\\n1. Read `report.nocolor.txt` — list failed tests with error messages, file:line references\\n2. Skip agents with zero failures\\n3. Build failure list: `[(test_name, agent, error_line, duration, file:line)]`\\n\\n### Step C3: Re-run Failing Tests via CI\\n\\nFor each failing test+agent pair, **sequentially**:\\n\\n1. **Trigger re-run:**\\n   ```bash\\n   gh workflow run e2e-isolated.yml -f agent=<agent> -f test=<TestName>\\n   ```\\n\\n2. **Wait for run to register** (~5s), then find the run ID:\\n   ```bash\\n   gh run list -w e2e-isolated.yml -L 1 --json databaseId -q '.[0].databaseId'\\n   ```\\n\\n3. **Poll until complete** (check every 30s, timeout after 25 minutes):\\n   ```bash\\n   gh run view <run-id> --json status,conclusion\\n   ```\\n\\n4. **Download re-run artifacts:**\\n   ```bash\\n   gh run download <run-id> --dir <rerun-artifact-dir>\\n   ```\\n\\n5. **Repeat for a second re-run** (same test+agent).\\n\\n### Step C4: Collect Results\\n\\nFor each test+agent pair, record: `(test, agent, original_result, rerun_1_result, rerun_2_result)`\\n\\nProceed to **Shared Analysis** (Step 1 below).\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Shared Analysis & Classification\\n\\n### Step 1: Analyze Each Failure\\n\\nFor each failure, follow the **Debugging Workflow** in `.claude/skills/debug-e2e/SKILL.md` (steps 2-5: console.log → test source → entire.log → deep dive). Collect:\\n- What the agent actually did (from console.log)\\n- What was expected (from test source)\\n- CLI-level errors or anomalies (from entire.log)\\n- Repo/checkpoint state (from git-log.txt, git-tree.txt, checkpoint-metadata/)\\n\\n### Step 2: Classify Each Failure\\n\\nUse **re-run results as the primary signal**, supplemented by artifact analysis.\\n\\n#### Re-run signals (strongest):\\n\\n| Original | Re-run 1 | Re-run 2 | Classification |\\n|----------|----------|----------|----------------|\\n| FAIL | FAIL (same error) | FAIL (same error) | **real-bug** OR **flaky (test-bug)** — see below |\\n| FAIL | PASS | PASS | **flaky** |\\n| FAIL | PASS | FAIL | **flaky** (non-deterministic) |\\n| FAIL | FAIL | PASS | **flaky** (non-deterministic) |\\n| FAIL | FAIL (different error) | FAIL (different error) | **needs deeper analysis** — examine artifacts |\\n\\n**Important: Consistent failures can still be `flaky` (test-bug).** When all re-runs fail, check *where* the root cause is:\\n- Root cause in `cmd/entire/cli/` → **real-bug** (product code is broken)\\n- Root cause in `e2e/` (test infra, test helpers, tmux setup, env propagation) → **flaky (test-bug)** — the CLI works fine, the test is broken\\n\\n#### Strong `real-bug` signals (root cause must be in `cmd/entire/cli/`, not `e2e/`):\\n\\n- `entire.log` contains `\\\"level\\\":\\\"ERROR\\\"` or panic/stack traces from CLI code\\n- Checkpoint metadata structurally corrupt (malformed JSON, missing `checkpoint_id`/`strategy`)\\n- Session state file missing or malformed when expected\\n- Hooks did not fire at all (no `hook invoked` log entries)\\n- Shadow/metadata branch has wrong tree structure\\n- Same test fails across 3+ agents with same non-timeout symptom\\n- Error references CLI code (panic in `cmd/entire/cli/`)\\n\\n**Key question:** Is the bug in `cmd/entire/cli/` (product code) or in `e2e/` (test code)? Only the former is a `real-bug`.\\n\\n#### Strong `flaky` signals (unless overridden by real-bug):\\n\\n**Agent behavior (non-deterministic):**\\n- `signal: killed` (timeout)\\n- `context deadline exceeded` or `WaitForCheckpoint.*exceeded deadline`\\n- Agent asked for confirmation instead of acting\\n- Agent created file at wrong path / wrong name\\n- Agent produced no output\\n- Agent committed when it shouldn't have (or vice versa)\\n- Duration near timeout limit\\n\\n**Test-bug (consistent failure, but root cause is in `e2e/` not `cmd/entire/cli/`):**\\n- Agent \\\"Not logged in\\\" / auth errors → test env setup doesn't propagate auth credentials\\n- Env vars not propagated to agent session → tmux/test harness bug\\n- Error references test code (`e2e/`) not CLI code (`cmd/entire/cli/`)\\n- Test helper logic errors (wrong assertions, bad globs, incorrect expected values)\\n- Consistent failure BUT root cause traced to `e2e/` code, not `cmd/entire/cli/`\\n- Test setup/teardown issues (missing git config, temp dir cleanup, port conflicts)\\n\\n#### Ambiguous cases:\\n\\nRead `entire.log` carefully:\\n- If hooks fired correctly and metadata is valid -> lean **flaky**\\n- If hooks fired but produced wrong results -> lean **real-bug**\\n\\n### Step 3: Cross-Agent Correlation\\n\\nBefore acting, check correlations using re-run data:\\n- Same test fails for 3+ agents, all re-runs also fail -> strong **real-bug**\\n- Same test fails for multiple agents, but re-runs pass -> **flaky** (shared prompt issue)\\n- One agent fails consistently, others pass -> agent-specific issue (still **real-bug** if re-runs confirm)\\n\\n### Step 4a: Take Action — Local Mode\\n\\nIn local mode, present findings interactively. **Do not** create branches, PRs, or GitHub issues.\\n\\n#### Present Findings Report\\n\\nFor each test+agent pair, print a findings block:\\n\\n```\\n## <TestName> (<agent>) — <classification>\\n\\n**Re-run results:** original=FAIL, rerun1=PASS, rerun2=PASS\\n**Evidence:**\\n- <1-2 sentence summary of what went wrong>\\n- <key artifact evidence: entire.log excerpt, console.log excerpt, etc.>\\n```\\n\\n#### For `flaky` failures: describe the proposed fix\\n\\nFor agent-behavior flaky issues, fixes typically modify test prompts. For test-bug flaky issues, fixes target `e2e/` infrastructure code (harness setup, helpers, env propagation).\\n\\n```\\n**Proposed fix:** <description>\\n  - File: <path to test file or e2e infrastructure file>\\n  - Change: <what will be modified — e.g., append \\\"Do not ask for confirmation\\\" to prompt, or fix env propagation in NewTmuxSession>\\n```\\n\\nCommon flaky fixes (same as CI mode):\\n- Agent asked for confirmation -> append \\\"Do not ask for confirmation\\\" to prompt\\n- Agent wrote to wrong path -> be more explicit about paths in prompt\\n- Agent committed when shouldn't -> add \\\"Do not commit\\\" to prompt\\n- Checkpoint wait timeout -> increase timeout argument\\n- Agent timeout (signal: killed) -> increase per-test timeout, simplify prompt\\n- Auth/env not propagated -> fix test harness env setup in `e2e/` code\\n- Test helper bug (wrong assertion, bad glob) -> fix test helper in `e2e/`\\n- tmux session setup issue -> fix `NewTmuxSession` or session config in `e2e/`\\n\\n#### For `real-bug` failures: describe root cause analysis\\n\\n```\\n**Root cause analysis:**\\n  - Component: <hooks | session | checkpoint | strategy | agent>\\n  - Suspected location: <file:function>\\n  - Description: <what's wrong and why>\\n  - Proposed fix: <what code change would address it>\\n```\\n\\n#### Ask the user\\n\\nPrompt the user:\\n\\n> **Should I fix these?**\\n> - [list of tests with classifications]\\n> - You can select all, specific tests, or skip.\\n\\nWait for user response before proceeding.\\n\\n#### Apply fixes (if user approves)\\n\\nFor **flaky** fixes the user approved:\\n1. Apply fixes directly in the working tree (no branch creation)\\n2. Run verification:\\n   ```bash\\n   mise run test:e2e:canary   # Must pass\\n   mise run fmt && mise run lint\\n   ```\\n3. If canary fails, investigate and adjust. Report what happened to the user.\\n\\nFor **real-bug** fixes the user approved:\\n1. Apply the fix directly in the working tree (no branch creation)\\n2. Run relevant tests to verify:\\n   ```bash\\n   mise run test        # Unit tests\\n   mise run test:e2e:canary  # Canary tests\\n   ```\\n3. Report results to the user.\\n\\n### Step 4b: Take Action — CI Mode\\n\\n#### For `flaky` failures: Batched PR\\n\\n1. Create branch `fix/e2e-flaky-<run-id-or-date>`\\n2. Apply fixes to ALL flaky test files (one branch, one PR):\\n   - Agent asked for confirmation -> append \\\"Do not ask for confirmation\\\" to prompt\\n   - Agent wrote to wrong path -> be more explicit about paths in prompt\\n   - Agent committed when shouldn't -> add \\\"Do not commit\\\" to prompt\\n   - Checkpoint wait timeout -> increase timeout